Enable Sharing Inheritance
Turn on sharing inheritance and select the objects to use as a sharing source. Sharing inheritance is on by default in new Salesforce orgs.
Test your particular use cases against your orgâ€™s security model and data to make sure that sharing inheritance works for you.

From Setup, enter Analytics, and click Settings.
Select Inherit sharing from Salesforce, and click Save.
Enable Sharing Inheritance for Synced Objects
In CRM Analytics Studio, click Data Manager.
Click Connect.
On the row for the object you want to enable, click the dropdown list.
Click Row Level Sharing.
Click Sharing inheritance on.
Click Save.
